{
  "text": "Asian patients with diabetes continue to exhibit high risk for renal complications. [CITATION_1] In observational studies as well as clinical trials, Asian patients with diabetes were more likely to develop end stage renal disease (ESRD) than their Caucasian counterparts. In a 25-year prospective survey, 60% of young Japanese patients with type 2 diabetes diagnosed before age 35 became blind or had developed ESRD at a mean age of 50. (61) ",
